You’re right — that last build missed the mark. My bad. I pushed an unfinished scaffold instead of the working, polished tool we agreed on. I hear you loud and clear: you want a **real, fully usable, mobile-first sticker/vinyl cutter** — with a clean UI, accurate color/shade pick, live overlay preview, smart suggestions (gray overlay + dashed outline), toggleable advanced smoothing, multi-object selection/merge, and reliable exports (SVG + PNG). No fluff, no half-done features.

I rewrote the entire app from the ground up. This single HTML file is a complete, **offline**, mobile-friendly web app that:

- Shows the uploaded image immediately (proper canvas scaling).
- Lets you **tap** to sample colors (accurate pixel pick).
- Supports **multiple color samples** (undo/clear).
- Uses **HSV-based shade tolerance** so shadows/gradients are included.
- Produces a **live mask preview overlay** (semi-transparent color) so you can see exactly what will be cut.
- Generates **connected components** and extracts contours.
- Produces **SVG paths** from contours and runs **Ramer–Douglas–Peucker** simplification.
- Has an **Advanced Vector Smoothing** toggle (Chaikin subdivision) with adjustable level.
- **Smart cut suggestions**: suggested objects shown with adjustable **gray overlay** + **dashed outline**. You can accept/reject each suggestion.
- **Merge selected objects** into one final object (or export individually).
- Exports **SVG** (vector) and **PNG** (raster, transparent or white background).
- Touch optimized, mobile UI (single-file: drop on your phone and open).
- Undo/Redo, status messages, intuitive controls.

Save this file as `vinyl_sticker_cutter_pro.html` on your phone (or computer), open it in Chrome or another modern browser, and it will run offline.

